Brabus Logo BRABUS GmbH is a German high-performance automotive aftermarket tuning company founded in 1977 in Bottrop. Brabus specializes in Mercedes-Benz, Smart and Maybach vehicles. Brabus is the largest Mercedes-Benz tuner after Mercedes-AMG, which has been a Daimler AG subsidiary since the 1990s. Source
